<emphasis id="E9CE3F4D09115B2D5490E043E40AF991" box="[197,340,1632,1657]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Distribution</emphasis>
. 
<collectingCountry id="A3ADA3CF09115B2D553EE043E487F992" box="[363,473,1632,1658]" name="Australia" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Australia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="A3ADA3CF09115B2D55B0E043E72AF992" box="[485,628,1632,1658]" name="Madagascar" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, New 
<collectingCountry id="A3ADA3CF09115B2D56EAE043E648F992" box="[703,790,1632,1658]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Guinea</collectingCountry>
, Oriental region and Tropical Africa (
<bibRefCitation id="BF2B9EAE09115B2D5085E043E032F992" author="Young, D. A." box="[1232,1388,1632,1658]" pageId="12" pageNumber="47" pagination="1 - 21" refId="ref6543" refString="Young, D. A. (1979) A review of the leafhopper genus Cofana. Proceedings of Entomological Society of Washington. 81, 1 - 21." type="journal article" year="1979">Young, 1979</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DB05E35F09115B2D5490E0ABE165F852" blockId="12.[151,1437,826,2018]" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="E9CE3F4D09115B2D5490E0ABE475F949" box="[197,299,1672,1697]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Remarks</emphasis>
. The 
<typeStatus id="04015DFD09115B2D5523E0ABE4F6F94A" box="[374,424,1672,1698]" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="1CBA98DC09115B2D5585E0ABE7DAF949" authorityName="Young" authorityYear="1979" box="[464,644,1672,1697]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cofana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unimaculata">
<emphasis id="E9CE3F4D09115B2D5585E0ABE7DAF949" box="[464,644,1672,1697]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">C. unimaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(in NMW) is a female, in relatively poor condition and therefore it is difficult to see characters properly (M.R. Wilson personal communication). Our interpretation of this species is based on the female and male specimens collected from 
<collectingRegion id="197E2DBD09115B2D57C2E0FBE170F91A" box="[919,1070,1752,1778]" country="India" name="West Bengal" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">West Bengal</collectingRegion>
(Calcutta and Kalyani respectively), place from which the 
<typeStatus id="04015DFD09115B2D55A3E123E776F8F2" box="[502,552,1792,1818]" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">type</typeStatus>
specimen comes. The absence of a median apical spot on the crown is the most distinguishing character that separates 
<taxonomicName id="1CBA98DC09115B2D56C8E10BE60FF8A9" authorityName="Young" authorityYear="1979" box="[669,849,1832,1857]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cofana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unimaculata">
<emphasis id="E9CE3F4D09115B2D56C8E10BE60FF8A9" box="[669,849,1832,1857]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">C. unimaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from other species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="1CBA98DC09115B2D509AE10BE0C2F8AA" authority="Melichar." authorityName="Melichar." box="[1231,1436,1832,1858]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cofana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E9CE3F4D09115B2D509AE10BE07BF8A9" box="[1231,1317,1832,1857]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Cofana</emphasis>
Melichar.
</taxonomicName>
Key features such as shape of female seventh sternite and male abdominal apodemes described by 
<bibRefCitation id="BF2B9EAE09115B2D5146E173E446F87A" author="Ramakrishnan, U." pageId="12" pageNumber="47" pagination="129 - 131" refId="ref6330" refString="Ramakrishnan, U. (1985) A new species of the genus Cofana Melichar (Cicadellidae: Cicadelloidea: Homoptera) from India. Journal of Entomological research, 9, 129 - 131." type="journal article" year="1985">Ramakrishnan (1985)</bibRefCitation>
to differentiate 
<taxonomicName id="1CBA98DC09115B2D5580E15BE726F879" authorityName="Ramakrishnan" authorityYear="1985" box="[469,632,1912,1937]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cofana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="karjatensis">
<emphasis id="E9CE3F4D09115B2D5580E15BE726F879" box="[469,632,1912,1937]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">C. karjatensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="1CBA98DC09115B2D5697E15BE629F879" authorityName="Young" authorityYear="1979" box="[706,887,1912,1937]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cofana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unimaculata">
<emphasis id="E9CE3F4D09115B2D5697E15BE629F879" box="[706,887,1912,1937]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">C. unimaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are found not to be discrete. In the absence of more convincing evidence, we treat this species as synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="1CBA98DC09115B2D572AE183E16AF851" authorityName="Young" authorityYear="1979" box="[895,1076,1952,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cofana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unimaculata">
<emphasis id="E9CE3F4D09115B2D572AE183E16AF851" box="[895,1076,1952,1977]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">C. unimaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DB05E35F09115B2D5493E1EBE137F80A" blockId="12.[151,1437,826,2018]" box="[198,1129,1992,2018]" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">
<taxonomicName id="1CBA98DC09115B2D5493E1EBE424F809" authorityName="Young" authorityYear="1979" box="[198,378,1992,2017]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cofana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unimaculata">
<emphasis id="E9CE3F4D09115B2D5493E1EBE424F809" box="[198,378,1992,2017]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">C. unimaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a common species on rice in Asia (
<bibRefCitation id="BF2B9EAE09115B2D5763E1EBE102F80A" author="Wilson, M. R. &amp; Claridge, M. F." box="[822,1116,1992,2018]" pageId="12" pageNumber="47" refId="ref6366" refString="Wilson, M. R. &amp; Claridge, M. F. (1991) Handbook for the identification of leafhoppers and plant hoppers of rice. CAB International Institute of Entomology in association with Natural Resources Institute, 142 pp." type="book" year="1991">Wilson &amp; Claridge 1991</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
